arXiv:2604.22079v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: The Belle and Belle~II experiments have accumulated a combined data set of $1.2~\mathrm{ab}^{-1}$ of $e^+e^- 	o B ar{B}$ collisions at the $\Upsilon(4S)$ resonance. Owing to the clean event environment and the well-constrained initial-state kinematics, these data are particularly well suited for studying channels involving missing energy from neutrinos. This includes the reinterpretation of $B^+	o K^+
u ar{
u}$ and the first inclusive measurement of $B	o X_s
u ar{
u}$ with the missing energy directly from $B$ decays, as well as searches involving missing energy from $	au$ decays, such as $B^0	o K^{*0}	au^+	au^-$, $B^0	o K_S^{0}	au^+	au^-$, and $B^+	o K^{+}	au^+	au^-$.
